    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Attractive and delicate purplish-red species forming flat, fern-like fronds. Main axes segmented (but nor banded in colour) and give off alternating lateral branches to left and right, but all in the same plane, at intervals of 3-4 segments. These re-branch several times into fairly dense tufts, but tips are not strongly incurved (as in many other <i>Ceramium</i> species).</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_7574",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Reaches about 200 mm on west coast, but much smaller on south coast. Main branches about 1 mm wide.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_7575",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Southern Africa and Antarctica. Also reported from Mozambique, but that record is considered suspect.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u><i> </i>Namibia to about Algoa Bay.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_7576",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Primarily a west coast species and often epiphytic of other algae. Common in low intertidal and subtidal reefs.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_7577",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Photosynthetic.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_7578",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Tetraspores borne externally around the branches of the axes.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_7579",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>The branching pattern is distinctive, but there are several other similar regional species in this and closely-related genera – see Stegenga reference for a more detailed account of and identification key to west coast species.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_7580",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Further reading / References",
            "shortText": "Anderson, RJ, Stegenga, H & Bolton, JJ (2016). Seaweeds of the South African South Coast. World Wide Web electronic publication, University of Cape Town, http://southafrseaweeds.uct.ac.za; Accessed on 22 July 2024.<br><br>Branch, G, Griffiths, CL, Branch, M & Beckley, L (2016). Two Oceans: A Guide to the Marine Life of Southern Africa (Fourth edition). Struik Nature, Cape Town. (p. 412). <br><br>Simons, RH (1966). The genus <i>Ceramium</i> in South Africa. <i>Bothalia</i>, 9, 153-168.<br><br>Stegenga, H, Bolton, J & Anderson, R (1997). Seaweeds of the South African west coast. <i>Contributions of the Bolus Herbarium</i>, 18. (p. 423).",
